{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "c3f7ec4d-1f66-4d59-9c4b-dc7fd8e5bb01",
    "name": "Kapomatic Warehouse API",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": "Collection for Warehouse backend APIs (categories, customers, products, credit-sales, and sellings), updated to match current request fields and filters. Customer details now return lastCreditSaleDate, lastCashSaleDate, lastCreditSalePaymentDate, and creditSummary with debtStatusSummary, totalDebtAmount, paidAmount, remainingAmount, totalRefundDueAmount, totalReturnedPaidAmount, and totalReallocatedPaidAmount. Credit-sale requests support customer linking, payment registration, partial or full invoice refunds, refundDueAmount tracking, automatic returnedPaidAmount handling on full refunds, automatic reallocatedPaidAmount handling when a partial refund creates overpayment, invoice status changing to Reactionary on full return, and inventory deduction/restoration. Update Product applies newInventory only when the payload inventoryCount matches the product's current stored inventoryCount. Create Selling auto-creates or updates the customer by customerName and customerPhone, stores one invoice document with an items array, and Get All Sellings returns invoice items with productCode."
  },
